# Kavacha patch 0034 — Clear unpinned tabs on quit
#
# On quit, discard every non-pinned tab so the next launch restores ONLY the
# tabs the user deliberately pinned. Pinning becomes the explicit "keep this"
# gesture; ordinary browsing tabs do not accumulate across sessions.
#
# New process-singleton module KavachaSessionCleanup.sys.mjs observes
# "quit-application-granted" (quit committed, windows still alive, SessionStore
# final write not yet flushed) and removes non-pinned tabs from every browser
# window. SessionStore keeps its state live as tabs close, so its final write
# excludes them; pinned tabs remain and restore normally.
#
# Gated on pref kavacha.session.clear-unpinned-on-quit (default true) so it can
# be disabled without a rebuild. skipPermitUnload avoids beforeunload prompts
# blocking a quit the user already chose; closeWindowWithLastTab:false stops
# removeTab from tearing a window down mid-quit.
#
# NOTE: authored/validated by git-apply against browser/zen-upstream; NOT yet
# build- or Marionette-verified.
#
# Touches: src/zen/common/modules/ZenStartup.mjs (init the singleton per window),
# src/zen/common/moz.build (register the module),
# src/zen/common/sys/KavachaSessionCleanup.sys.mjs (new).
